node.text: On this episode of DMTV Milkshake, we talk to Melodie Leung, associate director with @zahahadidarchitects. node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we spoke to @bimmawilliams, co-founder and host of the @claimastories podcast. Claima — ”claima” as in “claim a seat at the table” — is a podcast with a mission: to give young BIPOC creatives the inspiration, and roadmap, they need to make good on their ambitions. Bimma joins us from the road — specifically from, a custom-rigged 1993 Mitsubishi Delica Starwagon rechristened as “Storytella,” his mobile podcast studio during a 30-day, four-city tour of the West Coast. Here, he gives his best advice for young BIPOC creatives looking for professional advancement and shares a few of the stories that have moved him most. \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.text:
🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

node.text: With fall emerging, Scandinavian design and feelings of hygge come to mind. And as we transition to a quieter, more tranquil time of year, so too does our monthly mood. To set the tone for our focus on natural tranquility, we bring you @villakuro. Situated in the remote desert landscape of Joshua Tree, California the Villa Kuro vacation home seems to have been transplanted from Japan. This desert abode was designed by Elaine Chao and Stanley Yang of @miniinno and inspired by nature and the Japanese philosophy of wabi-sabi which seeks to find beauty in imperfection. Filled with natural textures, warm and minimal interiors, and contemporary furnishings, Villa Kuro is the picture-perfect escape away from the city. \\\ Read more about Villa Kuro at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Another design force looking to make an impact, @mon.terra was founded by Tamara Efrat, a multidisciplinary designer and entrepreneur, and Yuval Dishon, a process engineer and maker. Both hail from Tel-Aviv, although they met in Boston during a three-month social entrepreneurship program and determined that their shared values and complementary skillset made them a perfect match. Together, they turn agricultural plastic waste into furniture and accessories. \\\ At the link in bio, read Design Milk Editor @katietreggiden.1's interview with Yuval and Tamara for our latest installment of Circular By Design. 🔗
